ğŸš€ **One-command multimodal semantic search across your entire data lake using BigQuery ML and Google Cloud AI.**

## ğŸ“¦ Installation

```bash
# Install from PyPI
pip install grepctl
```

## ğŸ¯ Quick Start - From Zero to Search in One Command

```bash
# Complete setup with automatic data ingestion
grepctl init all --bucket your-bucket --auto-ingest

# Start searching immediately
grepctl search "find all mentions of machine learning"
```

That's it! The system automatically:
- âœ… Enables all required Google Cloud APIs
- âœ… Creates BigQuery dataset and tables
- âœ… Deploys Vertex AI embedding models
- âœ… Ingests all 8 data modalities from your GCS bucket
- âœ… Generates 768-dimensional embeddings
- âœ… Configures semantic search with VECTOR_SEARCH

## ğŸ“Š What is grepctl?

`grepctl` is a utility that converts unstructured content in your data lake into a semantically searchable index with a single command: `grepctl ingest -b <bucket>`

It processes **8 different data types** automatically:
- ğŸ“„ **Text & Markdown** - Direct content extraction, preserving structure
- ğŸ“‘ **PDF Documents** - OCR via Google Document AI for text extraction
- ğŸ–¼ï¸ **Images** - Vision API extracts labels, text, objects, and faces
- ğŸµ **Audio Files** - Speech-to-Text API transcribes to searchable text
- ğŸ¬ **Video Files** - Video Intelligence API analyzes frames and transcribes speech
- ğŸ“Š **JSON & CSV** - Structured data parsing with field preservation

Each modality is converted to text, chunked intelligently, and embedded using Vertex AI's text-embedding-004 model (768 dimensions) for semantic understanding.

